headlines.description: Frankie Ferrari made a key 3-pointer as part of a big San Francisco run late in the second half, and then added a clinching layup with 58.5 seconds remaining, and the Dons held on to beat No. 15 Saint Mary's 70-63 on Thursday.
headlines.shortLinkText: San Francisco rallies to upset No. 15 Saint Mary's 70-63

headlines.description: Fard Muhammad scored 22 points and grabbed eight rebounds to help Binghamton snap its seven-game losing streak by beating Stony Brook 69-57 in an America East battle Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Muhammad helps Binghamton halt skid, tops Stony Brook 69-57

headlines.description: Jordon Varnado hit a jumper and Kevin Barker split a pair of free throws to complete a late Troy rally to slip past Coastal Carolina 66-65 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Troy rallies late to beat Coastal Carolina 66-65

headlines.description: Jordan Giles and Brandon McKissic each had 17 points and Isaiah Ross added 14 as UMKC beat Chicago State 76-67 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giles and McKissic combine for 34 as UMKC outlasts Cougars

headlines.description: C.J. Burks scored a career-high 36 points with six 3-pointers, Jon Elmore added 28 points, six assists and seven rebounds and Marshall defeated Rice 93-80 Thursday night.
Kenneth Ogbe scored 22 points with four 3-pointers, Brandon Randolph added 17 points, and Utah Valley snapped New Mexico State's 11-game win streak with an 86-79 victory on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Utah Valley beats New Mexico State 86-79

headlines.description: Bogdan Bliznyuk scored 19 points with six rebounds and five assists and Eastern Washington ended Montana's 13-game winning streak 74-65 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bliznyuk, E Washington end Montana streak at 13, 74-65

nowFeed.headline: Oklahoma's Trae Young, on his recent offensive struggles: "I’m getting guarded like nobody else in the country is being guarded, scouted on like no one else in the country. It’s a mystery coming out each and every game to try and figure out how a team is going to guard me and how I’m going to dictate how my team wins. … It’s a lot tougher for me to score now than it was in the beginning. ... It’s a process. Right now, it’s tough."
